cs.MS, cs.AR, cs.CE, cs.DC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation and performance analysis of a numerical algorithm (Kahan algorithm) for a scalar product kernel loop. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper describes the efficient SIMD-vectorized implementations on multi- and manycore processors, and discusses the impact of processor features on performance. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance characteristics of a numerical algorithm that is commonly used in scientific computing applications. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses thread-parallel execution and performance on multi- and manycore processors. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses low-level optimizations and performance modeling techniques for efficient implementation of the Kahan-enhanced scalar product.
